title: 289 - Chutes and Ladders
description:
"Don't get mad at me because I want to be my best every time I get on the court and you don't. Don't make me the villain because I wanna win and you don't want to win."
 In life, are you inconsistent in your execution and excellence? Do you allow the environment to determine your energy? In today's episode, the guys are breaking down the importance of being internally motivated to be successful. The difference between the good and the great is that the good need something to get them going, but the greats produce it internally.
